<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="939" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d939">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay.</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-29"><hi rend="italic">November 29,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 225.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At the request of the minister for foreign
                            affairs I have the honor to inclose two documents, copies of
                                attachments<note n="a" xml:id="d939fna">Not printed.</note> issued
                            by the <pb facs="0955" n="867" xml:id="pg_867"/> local courts here
                            against the property of the heirs of Henry F. Rudloff.</p>
                        <p>I am,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William W.
                            Russell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>